New Records: Trent Alexander-Arnold scored a stunning direct free-kick goal from 25 yards out for England, marking a significant achievement in the match.
Key Match Events: Jack Grealish opened the scoring with a low finish into the bottom corner after a flicked pass from Angel Gomes.
Declan Rice added to the score with a well-timed finish in the six-yard box after Ollie Watkins' cross.
Finland scored a late consolation goal through Arttu Hoskonen, heading home from a corner kick.
Pre-Game Insights: Lee Carsley made six changes to the England lineup following their previous defeat to Greece.
The match was England's attempt to regain control of their Nations League promotion chances.
Post-Match Reflections: England's victory was seen as a much-needed win, though not entirely convincing due to defensive lapses.
Manager Lee Carsley expressed concerns about the team's defensive performance.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match was part of the Nations League, with promotion still in England's hands after the win.
The game was notable for the high number of goals and the late goals scored by both teams.
